[{"type":"{{","value":[["pagebanner"],["S-amer africa default banner.jpg"],["pgname=Bathurst"]]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["Image:Bathurst1-wiki.jpg"],["thumb"],["right"],["300px"],["The Big Pineapple in Bathurst"]]}," \n",{"type":"'''","value":[{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.bathurst.co.za\/ Bathurst"]}]},", the pineapple capital of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["South Africa"]]}," is located in the ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Eastern Cape"]]},".\n\n\n\nBathurst was founded in 1820 and named after the colonial secretary of\nthe British government, Lord Bathurst. 10 Minutes from Port Alfred and\nhome to the oldest pub in South Africa, the townâ€™s major attraction is the\nBig Pineapple, which stands 16.7 metre high.\n\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get in"]},"\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["By plane"]},"\nThere are two airports located in close proximity to Bathurst. The closest is the East London airport which is 112km from Addo. The Port Elizabeth airport is 127km away. There are regular flights from ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Johannesburg"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Cape Town"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Durban"]]}," and other South African destinations to the airports in Port Elizabeth and East London.\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["By car"]},"\nBathurst is easily accessible by motorways from Cape Town (779km)or ",{"type":"[[","value":[["East London"]]}," (112km). You could also drive in from Johannesburg (818km). The road conditions are fairly good if you are coming from any of these cities.\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["By bus"]},"\nAll major South African coach companies offer regular schedules to and from destinations like ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Addo"]]},".\n\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get around"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["See"]},"\n\n",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Bradshaw's Mill"],["url="],["email="],["address="],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=A working watermill and Nat